                <h2>Health Challenges and Disease Prevention</h2>
                <p>Effective management of common diseases is crucial for the well-being of goats:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Caprine Arthritis Encephalitis (CAE):</strong> Regular screening and management of infected goats.</li>
                    <li><strong>Internal Parasites:</strong> Implement deworming protocols and manage pasture to reduce parasite load.</li>
                    <li><strong>Pneumonia:</strong> Ensure proper ventilation and manage stress to prevent respiratory issues.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Work with a veterinarian to establish a comprehensive health management plan.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

